odin has been installed under:

    /opt/odin

The packaged rc.d script is installed as:

    /usr/local/etc/rc.d/odin

Create service configs in:

    /opt/odin/etc/odin/services

A sample service config is available at:

    /opt/odin/etc/odin/services/hello.toml.sample

To enable the supervisor at boot:

    sysrc odin_enable=YES
    service odin start

The rc.d script runs:

    /opt/odin/bin/odin --config-dir /opt/odin/etc/odin/services --socket /var/run/odin.sock serve

Application logs are expected in /var/log/odin and can be rotated by the
packaged newsyslog configuration.
